<i>WHAT'S UP, PEOPLE?! !</i>

21
00:01:14,993 --> 00:01:19,330
<i>Are you worried?</i>

22
00:01:41,102 --> 00:01:44,147
How many seconds has it been
since you wrote down the first name?

23
00:01:46,899 --> 00:01:47,900
35...

24
00:01:48,276 --> 00:01:49,277
36...

25
00:01:49,652 --> 00:01:50,737
37...

26
00:01:51,195 --> 00:01:52,447
38!

27
00:01:53,031 --> 00:01:54,282
39!

28
00:01:54,657 --> 00:01:56,659
I win, Near!

29
00:01:57,076 --> 00:01:58,620
40!

30
00:01:58,745 --> 00:02:02,123
NEW WORLD

31
00:02:22,685 --> 00:02:23,770
We're not dead...

32
00:02:25,271 --> 00:02:26,439
A minute's passed...

33
00:02:26,648 --> 00:02:27,690
But we're not dead!

34
00:02:30,443 --> 00:02:33,363
I've been telling you that
nobody would die.

35
00:02:34,781 --> 00:02:36,658
W-Why?

36
00:02:37,533 --> 00:02:38,785
Why won't they die?!

37
00:02:40,161 --> 00:02:41,371
G-God!

38
00:02:41,788 --> 00:02:43,581
I did as you told me!

39
00:02:44,165 --> 00:02:45,792
Rester, Gevanni, apprehend Mikami.

40
00:02:53,257 --> 00:02:54,842
Gevanni, the notebook.

41
00:02:58,471 --> 00:03:00,473
See for yourselves.

42
00:03:01,224 --> 00:03:12,402
KANZO MOGI TOUTA MATSUDA
HIDEKI IDE SHUICHI AIZAWA

43
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:14,612
Light Yagami.

44
00:03:16,864 --> 00:03:18,950
Mikami called you "God,"

45
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:21,411
and said that he did
as you told him to...

46
00:03:22,995 --> 00:03:24,163
This proves it.

47
00:03:28,251 --> 00:03:29,460
It's a trap!

48
00:03:29,544 --> 00:03:30,628
This is a trap!

49
00:03:31,129 --> 00:03:33,673
Near set the whole thing up
to frame me!

50
00:03:34,298 --> 00:03:35,967
It's strange that no one's dead

51
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:37,510
even after their names
were written in the notebook.

52
00:03:37,635 --> 00:03:39,470
That proves that this is a trap!

53
00:03:44,517 --> 00:03:46,144
But I told you that nobody would die

54
00:03:46,227 --> 00:03:48,104
because I tampered
with the notebook.

55
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:51,524
N-No...

56
00:03:52,692 --> 00:03:53,693
This is impossible!

57
00:03:56,571 --> 00:03:59,157
This is a setup.
I don't know that man.

58
00:04:04,704 --> 00:04:07,790
Light, it's too late.
Near wins.

59
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:11,002
A second ago,
you said, "I win."

60
00:04:12,044 --> 00:04:14,046
That's as good a confession as any.

61
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:20,094
Light...

62
00:04:22,388 --> 00:04:23,639
W-Why?

63
00:04:31,898 --> 00:04:33,191
S-Stop it!

64
00:04:43,409 --> 00:04:46,287
Light Yagami. . .L...

65
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,414
Kira...

66
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:51,209
You lose.

67
00:04:54,754 --> 00:04:58,341
You claimed your victory
a moment ago.

68
00:04:58,966 --> 00:05:03,888
To tell the truth, you might actually
have won, and I might have lost.

69
00:05:05,515 --> 00:05:08,518
Things turned out exactly
as you had expected...

70
00:05:09,685 --> 00:05:11,521
And we tampered with
the fake notebook.

71
00:05:14,106 --> 00:05:17,193
But when I said that
I had tampered with it,

72
00:05:17,902 --> 00:05:20,196
I was referring to
the real notebook as well.

73
00:05:22,073 --> 00:05:24,283
We only switched a part
of the fake notebook.

74
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:25,910
But as for the real one...

75
00:05:26,285 --> 00:05:27,954
We replaced the whole thing.

76
00:05:28,913 --> 00:05:30,665
This is the real notebook.

77
00:05:32,124 --> 00:05:33,668
I-Impossible!

78
00:05:34,335 --> 00:05:39,090
We used the same pen as Mikami,
copied Mikami's handwriting to perfection,

79
00:05:39,423 --> 00:05:42,260
and made the inside and
outside look exactly the same...

80
00:05:43,094 --> 00:05:45,471
Gevanni was able to
do it overnight.

81
00:05:49,475 --> 00:05:52,103
Since I had already touched
the real notebook...

82
00:05:52,812 --> 00:05:55,022
I could see the Shinigami...

83
00:05:57,692 --> 00:06:00,611
Mr. Shinigami, pleased to meet you.
I'm Near.

84
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:04,907
Nice to meet you. I'm Ryuk.

85
00:06:05,658 --> 00:06:07,493
<i>He's talking to Ryuk...</i>

86
00:06:08,411 --> 00:06:10,788
<i>He can see him,
so he must be telling the truth...</i>

87
00:06:11,664 --> 00:06:15,042
The edges of this page of
the notebook are clipped.

88
00:06:15,459 --> 00:06:18,754
Would someone die if his name were
written on this clipped portion?

89
00:06:18,963 --> 00:06:20,631
Yeah. They'll die.

90
00:06:21,007 --> 00:06:22,216
I thought so...

91
00:06:22,717 --> 00:06:25,469
You probably found many ways
to use this...

92
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:29,765
I wonder how many times you've killed
and deceived us with this...

93
00:06:32,351 --> 00:06:35,813
Light Yagami. You are Kira.

94
00:06:40,693 --> 00:06:42,403
<i>There's got to be
some sort of trick behind this...</i>

95
00:06:43,279 --> 00:06:44,906
<i>Could Mikami have
double-crossed me?</i>

96
00:06:45,114 --> 00:06:46,240
You're wrong.

97
00:06:47,241 --> 00:06:48,701
I owe this to Mello.

98
00:06:49,911 --> 00:06:52,163
I'm sure you understand
what I mean by that.

99
00:06:53,247 --> 00:06:54,332
<i>Mel/o?!</i>

100
00:06:55,124 --> 00:06:56,667
Take a good look at this...

101
00:06:59,086 --> 00:07:01,756
KIYOMI TAKADA SUICIDE
BURNS TO DEATH

102
00:07:01,756 --> 00:07:01,797
Takada's name is in the notebook!

103
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,342
<i>A plan to kill Takada...</i>

104
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:06,510
<i>JANUARY 262:33 PM
a minute after I did!</i>

105
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:06,886
JANUARY 262:33 PM

106
00:07:07,553 --> 00:07:09,680
<i>Could it be that Mikami did
the same thing at that time?!</i>

107
00:07:11,849 --> 00:07:13,935
G-God, I thought that you were being
watched and couldn't take action...

108
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:18,856
I thought it was my job to take care
of Takada in a situation like that...

109
00:07:19,357 --> 00:07:20,358
<i>Idiot!</i>

110
00:07:20,483 --> 00:07:23,653
<i>I've been giving you orders to not
make any unnecessary moves until today!</i>

111
00:07:24,570 --> 00:07:25,655
That's right.

112
00:07:25,738 --> 00:07:29,367
On the 26th, right after Takada's
kidnapping was broadcast...

113
00:07:29,575 --> 00:07:31,869
Mikami went to the bank...

114
00:07:32,578 --> 00:07:34,038
According to my findings,

115
00:07:34,455 --> 00:07:37,541
Mikami goes to the bank
every month on the 25th.

116
00:07:38,042 --> 00:07:40,586
It is very odd for someone
as methodical as Mikami

117
00:07:40,711 --> 00:07:42,004
to go there for two days in a row.

118
00:07:43,005 --> 00:07:46,175
I followed Mikami to
a safe deposit box.

119
00:07:46,926 --> 00:07:49,011
It was only at this time that

120
00:07:49,095 --> 00:07:51,347
Mikami seemed nervous about
someone possibly following him...

121
00:07:53,391 --> 00:07:54,976
It was easy to open the safe.

122
00:07:55,393 --> 00:07:56,435
Inside it...

123
00:07:57,228 --> 00:08:01,315
The real notebook was there and
Takada's name was written in it...

124
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,235
Light Yagami.

125
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:08,864
You didn't notice that Mikami
took the liberty and made a move...

126
00:08:09,407 --> 00:08:12,368
because you had just killed her
with a clipping from the notebook...

127
00:08:13,786 --> 00:08:18,082
This is when I noticed the possibility
of a fake notebook...

128
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:20,584
Thanks to Mello...

129
00:08:21,335 --> 00:08:23,129
who was the one
who created this situation.

130
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:27,425
<i>Mello may have known about it...</i>

131
00:08:29,385 --> 00:08:32,388
<i>...by having his name
written in the notebook?</i>

132
00:08:32,888 --> 00:08:33,889
Yes...

133
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:37,727
Then I guess I'm going to
have to do it.

134
00:08:40,312 --> 00:08:42,106
Mello knew...

135
00:08:42,815 --> 00:08:48,529
He knew that alone, we aren't able
to attain our goal, to surpass L.

136
00:08:49,363 --> 00:08:50,948
But together...

137
00:08:51,866 --> 00:08:53,576
Together we can stand with L.

138
00:08:54,452 --> 00:08:55,953
Together we can surpass L!

139
00:08:56,287 --> 00:08:59,582
And right now, we are
confronting Kira who defeated L...

140
00:08:59,665 --> 00:09:01,625
with solid evidence!

141
00:09:05,504 --> 00:09:08,674
Let's see you talk your way
out of this if you can.

142
00:09:44,085 --> 00:09:45,127
That's right...

143
00:09:48,339 --> 00:09:49,840
I'm Kira.

144
00:10:02,311 --> 00:10:04,563
That's right. I'm Kira.

145
00:10:06,732 --> 00:10:08,067
So what are you going to do?

146
00:10:10,361 --> 00:10:11,570
Are you going to kill me here?

147
00:10:14,907 --> 00:10:17,576
Listen... I'm Kira.

148
00:10:17,993 --> 00:10:19,078
And...

149
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:23,040
I'm the god of the new world!

150
00:10:25,668 --> 00:10:28,254
Kira is the law of
the world right now.

151
00:10:28,379 --> 00:10:30,631
Kira is maintaining order.

152
00:10:31,465 --> 00:10:33,342
I am now Justice.

153
00:10:34,176 --> 00:10:36,137
The human race and
the world's only hope.

154
00:10:37,346 --> 00:10:38,347
Are you going to kill me?

155
00:10:40,182 --> 00:10:41,725
Is that really the right thing to do?

156
00:10:44,728 --> 00:10:47,064
Since Kira appeared six years ago...

157
00:10:47,189 --> 00:10:51,652
wars have stopped and global crime rates
have decreased by 70 percent.

158
00:10:52,236 --> 00:10:54,864
But the world is still rotten!

159
00:10:55,698 --> 00:10:57,533
There are too many
rotten people...

160
00:11:00,995 --> 00:11:03,038
Someone's got to do it.

161
00:11:04,123 --> 00:11:08,669
From the moment I got hold of
the notebook, I knew I had to do it!

162
00:11:08,836 --> 00:11:12,548
No, I was the only one
who could do it!

163
00:11:14,341 --> 00:11:16,760
I know that killing people
is a crime...

164
00:11:18,387 --> 00:11:21,599
But this is the only way
to fix the world!

165
00:11:21,682 --> 00:11:23,601
This is a duty given to me!

166
00:11:25,978 --> 00:11:27,730
I'm the only one who can do this!

167
00:11:29,648 --> 00:11:32,693
Could anyone else have done it?!
Could they have done this much?!

168
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:34,195
Could they have continued on?!

169
00:11:37,072 --> 00:11:38,324
That's right...

170
00:11:39,491 --> 00:11:44,914
I'm the only one who can
create the new world...

171
00:11:50,961 --> 00:11:53,923
No. You are just a murderer.

172
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:59,637
And this notebook is
the worst murder weapon in history.

173
00:12:01,013 --> 00:12:03,766
You've yielded to the power
of the Shinigami and the notebook.

174
00:12:04,516 --> 00:12:07,102
You're just a crazy serial killer

175
00:12:07,186 --> 00:12:09,438
who has confused himself with a god.

176
00:12:10,147 --> 00:12:11,815
That's all you are...

177
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:15,027
Nothing more, nothing less.

178
00:12:31,752 --> 00:12:34,171
<i>They're all fools who don't understand.</i>

179
00:12:50,813 --> 00:12:52,022
Near.

180
00:12:53,274 --> 00:12:55,567
The notebook you have right now,
and the notebook that

181
00:12:56,193 --> 00:12:59,613
Aizawa brought from the Japanese
Task Force Headquarters...

182
00:13:00,990 --> 00:13:02,241
Are they real?

183
00:13:03,701 --> 00:13:05,327
<i>Is he bluffing now?</i>

184
00:13:06,662 --> 00:13:08,914
Only I know where
the real notebook is...

185
00:13:12,209 --> 00:13:14,128
If you're going to defeat Kira...

186
00:13:14,420 --> 00:13:17,131
even if it's just to test out
the notebook that Aizawa's carrying...

187
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:23,804
you should write either
my name or Mikami's in it.

188
00:13:27,933 --> 00:13:30,436
To see if the notebook is real...

189
00:13:32,354 --> 00:13:33,564
or fake!

190
00:13:35,065 --> 00:13:36,108
He's hidden
a piece of the notebook!

191
00:13:39,778 --> 00:13:40,863
Matsuda!

192
00:13:45,868 --> 00:13:47,870
You idiot!

193
00:13:48,203 --> 00:13:50,914
Matsuda! Who do you think
you're shooting at?!

194
00:13:51,457 --> 00:13:53,250
Stop messing around!

195
00:13:55,544 --> 00:13:56,920
What was it all for?

196
00:13:57,963 --> 00:14:00,966
What in the world did
your dad die for?

197
00:14:01,717 --> 00:14:02,634
Dad?!

198
00:14:03,052 --> 00:14:05,929
Oh, you mean Soichiro Yagami?!

199
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,265
That's right, Matsuda!

200
00:14:08,766 --> 00:14:11,310
Overly earnest people with
a strong sense of justice like him

201
00:14:11,435 --> 00:14:12,644
are always going to lose.

202
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:15,314
Are you okay with
a world like that?!

203
00:14:15,439 --> 00:14:18,942
Kill the others if you understand!

204
00:14:19,485 --> 00:14:21,111
Shoot!

205
00:14:22,738 --> 00:14:24,907
You let your father die...

206
00:14:25,657 --> 00:14:27,826
How can you act as if
it were nothing?!

207
00:14:33,582 --> 00:14:34,625
He's writing with his blood!

208
00:14:41,465 --> 00:14:42,466
I'm going to kill you!

209
00:14:42,591 --> 00:14:44,676
We have to kill him!

210
00:14:45,052 --> 00:14:46,345
Matsuda!

211
00:15:07,908 --> 00:15:09,243
Damn it...

212
00:15:09,368 --> 00:15:12,371
What...the hell is this?!

213
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:19,878
Mikami... What are you doing?!

214
00:15:20,879 --> 00:15:22,047
Write!

215
00:15:22,589 --> 00:15:26,176
Kill. . ihem!

216
00:15:30,639 --> 00:15:33,225
Near, it's finally over, isn't it?

217
00:15:34,226 --> 00:15:35,269
Yes.

218
00:15:39,481 --> 00:15:41,108
What happened to Misa?!

219
00:15:42,025 --> 00:15:43,819
What about Takada?!

220
00:15:49,241 --> 00:15:52,035
<i>S-Somebody...</i>

221
00:15:54,246 --> 00:15:57,541
<i>What in the world should I. . . ?</i>

222
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:13,682
M-Mikami is...

223
00:16:17,227 --> 00:16:18,270
Stop the bleeding!

224
00:16:18,395 --> 00:16:19,563
No, but...

225
00:16:20,481 --> 00:16:21,523
There's nothing we can do...

226
00:16:37,247 --> 00:16:38,332
Light!

227
00:16:41,043 --> 00:16:42,503
Light! Wait!

228
00:16:42,628 --> 00:16:43,629
Mr. Aizawa!

229
00:16:44,963 --> 00:16:47,466
He probably doesn't have
any more notebooks hidden.

230
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:50,802
He can't go very far
with those wounds.

231
00:16:51,345 --> 00:16:53,639
He'll stop on his own
if we leave him alone.

232
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:58,185
Near, I'm not taking your orders.

233
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:03,357
I understand. I'll leave it to you.

234
00:18:42,205 --> 00:18:44,625
<i>You lose, Light.</i>

235
00:18:46,501 --> 00:18:48,045
<i>I told you when we first met,</i>

236
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:52,382
<i>that I'd be the one writing
your name...</i>

237
00:18:52,507 --> 00:18:54,718
<i>in my notebook when you die.</i>

238
00:18:57,095 --> 00:18:59,306
<i>That's the rule between</i>

239
00:18:59,431 --> 00:19:01,266
<i>the Shinigami who brings the notebook
into the Human Realm...</i>

240
00:19:03,101 --> 00:19:07,522
<i>and the first human
who picks up the notebook.</i>

241
00:19:09,608 --> 00:19:12,694
<i>If they put you in prison,
who knows when you'll die?</i>

242
00:19:13,904 --> 00:19:15,781
<i>And that would be too much of
a pain to wait around for.</i>

243
00:19:17,991 --> 00:19:20,035
<i>It's all over for you.</i>

244
00:19:23,664 --> 00:19:24,915
<i>You should die right here.</i>

245
00:19:32,631 --> 00:19:37,719
<i>We Were able to ease each ofheris
boredom for a long time.</i>

246
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:45,727
<i>It was a lot of fun.</i>

247
00:19:45,894 --> 00:19:47,020
LIGHT YAGAMI

